        ".     In March 1891 he received his doctorate in Romance Philology  with a dissertation on the dialect of Agrigento: Sounds and Developments of Sounds in the Speech of Craperallis.       After a brief sojourn in Sicily, during which the planned marriage with his cousin was finally called off, he returned to Rome, where he became friends with a group of writer-journalists including Ugo Fleres, Tomaso Gnoli, Giustino Ferri and ": null
